{"source_hash": "7fd0e9cab2ee999f", "candidate": {"id": "cand-016", "name": "Kwame Adjei", "raw_cv": "KWAME ADJEI\nkwame.adjei@email.com | Remote (London, UK)\n\nML ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nML engineer with 5 years of experience in NLP and applied ML for content moderation and trust & safety systems. Strong Python and PyTorch skills with good experience in MLflow and model deployment pipelines. Values-aligned professional.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nML Engineer \u2014 TikTok (ByteDance), London (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained multilingual content classification models for trust & safety (NSFW, misinformation, violence)\n- Led model evaluation and bias auditing for EU DSA compliance\n- Deployed ONNX-optimised models to low-latency serving infrastructure\n- Managed experiment tracking in MLflow across a team of 6 engineers\n\nML Engineer \u2014 Jigsaw (Google), London (2019\u20132021)\n- Developed perspective API models for toxicity detection\n- Built training data pipelines for multilingual hate speech classifiers\n\nSKILLS\nPython, PyTorch, ONNX, MLflow, Hugging Face Transformers, NumPy, Docker, Kubernetes, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Data Science \u2014 Imperial College London (2018\u20132019)\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 University of Ghana (2014\u20132018)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nGhanaian national, UK Global Talent visa", "raw_linkedin": "ML engineer working on trust & safety and content moderation AI. Currently at TikTok in London working on multilingual classification systems for the EU market. Five years of experience in applied ML \u2014 mostly NLP but with a growing interest in perception systems. UK-based on a Global Talent visa. I'm selective about employers \u2014 I care about the impact of the technology I work on and the environmental commitments of my employer. Open to senior ML engineer roles at organisations with strong ethical and environmental credentials.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Kwame, thanks for coming in. Your content moderation background is quite different from our perception work \u2014 tell me how you see the connection.\n\nKwame: The core ML engineering skills are highly transferable \u2014 PyTorch, ONNX deployment, MLflow, model evaluation rigour. The domain is different but I've been studying computer vision on the side and I worked with some image-based classifiers at Jigsaw. I think the transition is manageable for someone with strong fundamentals.\n\nInterviewer: The role involves defence applications. I want to ask directly \u2014 do you have any concerns about the nature of the work?\n\nKwame: I do want to think through that carefully. I care about the real-world impact of what I work on. Public safety applications I'm fully comfortable with. Lethal autonomous systems I would not want to be involved in. Can you tell me more about the specific end-use of the perception system?\n\nInterviewer: Our systems are primarily used for border security, surveillance, and ISR \u2014 intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance. Not weapons targeting.\n\nKwame: That's helpful context. ISR and border security I can work with, as long as there are ethical oversight frameworks.\n\nInterviewer: The 2-days-onsite arrangement works for you?\n\nKwame: Cambridge is doable. But I should mention something important to me that I want to be upfront about. I have a strong requirement to work for an employer that is committed to net-zero carbon operations and ideally has third-party verified environmental credentials. It's not negotiable for me \u2014 it's a core part of how I make career decisions. I'd want to see Stratagem's environmental commitments before accepting any offer.\n\nInterviewer: We're a defence contractor \u2014 our carbon footprint is not something we've formally committed to measuring publicly. We do have internal sustainability policies.\n\nKwame: I see. That's something I'd need to investigate further. It's a significant factor for me.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nKwame: I'm at \u00a382,000. I'd need \u00a388\u201395,000 given the domain learning and potential clearance process.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "PyTorch", "ONNX", "MLflow", "Hugging Face Transformers", "NumPy", "Docker", "Kubernetes", "Git", "NLP", "content moderation", "model evaluation", "bias auditing", "model deployment", "computer vision"], "industries": ["AI/ML", "content moderation", "trust & safety", "defence"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.78, "culture_fit_score": 0.65, "constraints": [{"id": "368eb219", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a382,000; minimum expectation stated in interview", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "b35bc1a4", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary requirement \u00a388\u201395k for new role with domain learning and clearance process", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96}, {"id": "e4425db5", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Upper salary expectation \u00a388\u201395k", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96}, {"id": "dc367900", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "ethics", "description": "Non-negotiable requirement: employer must have net-zero carbon operations commitment with third-party verified environmental credentials", "canonical_key": "carbon_neutral_employer", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "b3e47610", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "ethics", "description": "Will not work on lethal autonomous weapons systems; comfortable with border security, surveillance, and ISR applica